Dialogs.Dialog: Manaka
Hey, lately, have you found anything interesting on TV？
Huh？ ▲高嶺＊＊▲ but at your house...
Yeah, the channels that I can watch have already been decided.
But if there's any program you find interesting, I might ask for permission from my parents so that I can watch it, too.
I see.
But, it would be better if it's not variety show...
Ah, romance drama isn't good either...
If it's an intellectual quiz show or cooking show, it might be easier to ask them.
What do you think？
(Honestly, this is just a little too difficult...)
Manaka
Earlier, I asked you whether you knew any interesting TV program. Did you remember？
Yeah, I remembered. Why？
Well, I asked Mama to help me talk to Papa about it. She did, but...
They started to quarrel because of that.
Ah, so it's really difficult to persuade your father, huh？
No, Papa isn't as strict as you might think he is.
Then why？
Now Mama, who usually has a smile on her face, seems to be very upset but she didn't tell me why...
I already apologized to her because it was my fault asking her to talk with Papa about the TV program.
But I don't think the TV program is the problem here. I really don't know what to do...
(Somehow, it turned into a family problem...)
Hey, have your parents reconciled yet？
Manaka
No... not yet.
I see...
Ah, but they said okay to the cooking show. Only once per week, but that's good enough.
Wow, you did it ！
Hehe, thanks. It's thanks to your cooperation.
But how come your parents still haven't reconciled？
Papa didn't have a clue why Mama was so angry.
Papa told me that he might have said something that he shouldn't have said... but he had no idea what it was.
Mama only said, "I don't know why men are always like this." and continued being angry with Papa.
(I have to be careful about this...)
Has peace returned to the Takanes yet？
Manaka
Yeah, finally. Thanks for asking.
Did your parents find the cause of their argument？
I guess so... Mama didn't tell me, though.
Why？
It seems that it's a secret between my parents.
It was the first time I saw them quarreled, so I didn't know what to do. But they said that I shouldn't be worried.
Haha, I see. But it's good that they reconciled.
Yeah. Now they've become so lovey-dovey and I start to think that quarrelling wasn't totally a bad thing.
Y-You mean...
Hehe. Just kidding. We'll always be nice to each other, okay？
Manaka
Hey, how much do you know about cell phones？
Eh？ Why？
Papa asked me how to change the ring tone, but...
I didn't know how to do that.
Did you read the manual？
We tried to find it but we couldn't. Papa probably threw it away after he finished using it.
I couldn't even change a single ring tone and he asked me to personalize each ring tone for each caller.
Hah... I'll have to try and find the manual...
(This seems like a difficult job for her...)
By the way, did you find the cell phone's manual？
Manaka
No. But, I finally managed to change the default ring tone to something else.
How did you do that？
Papa and I were trying different settings until it worked, but it's still difficult to assign ring tones for each caller.
I see...
I suggested that he should take it to the store, but he didn't want to.
...He'd be ashamed, right？
You know a lot, huh？ I think Papa won't give up until he can change it by himself.
He's such a stubborn person, so it can't be helped, huh？
(▲高嶺＊＊▲'s unyielding spirit is probably heredity.)
Did you figure out how to change the ring tone？
Manaka
I finally did.
Oh, as I expected. Now your dad can feel at ease now, right？
That's...
He has become even more stubborn.
Ah...
I kind of understand him so I didn't say anything.
Even if he finds the manual, he probably won't use it. I wonder if he's still fumbling with it now...
(In the end, things became even more complicated for him, huh...？)
How was your dad after the issue with the cell phone？
Manaka
Well... Mama ended up changing the ring tone for him.
Eh！？
And, while Papa was still shocked to speak, Mama just explained to him how to change it.
He didn't get mad at all？
No. He just said "Okay" and obediently took the cell phone from Mama. He even thanked her properly.
Hmm...？ Compared to what you told me about him earlier, I'd say that this is very unexpected.
Mama said that for a person like Papa, he had to take it the hard way. She told me it was called "Shock Therapy."
Your mom really knows how to handle him.
It seemed like she found the manual and learned how to do it. Now everything is settled, I think.
(When I have a chance to meet her mom, I'd better learn something from her.)
Manaka
Ah, right. I have to return a recipe book to Miki-chan.
Miki-chan？
Yeah. I haven't told you about her？
This is the first time I've heard you mentioned this name.
I see. Well, she's been my friend since grade school. We go to different high schools, but we still keep in touch.
She said that she has never read this book after she bought it, and she lent it to me.
She has never read it...？ That means it's like a brand new book？
Yeah, she felt satisfied just to have the book.
That's the feeling I can never understand. She is very different from me but that makes it really fun to talk with her. Hehe.
(So she's like the exact opposite of you, huh？)
Manaka
I met up with Miki-chan earlier.
Ah, the girl who's like the exact opposite of ▲高嶺＊＊▲, right？
Hehe. Right. I went to return the book to her but ended up borrowing another recipe book from her.
Eh？ Is it another brand new book that she has never read？
No, she tried the recipes in this book so many times but her attempts always failed.
She asked me to be her coach, so I'll have to try these recipes by myself first.
Be her coach？
Yeah. She wants to make pudding for the guy she likes. I'll try my best to help her. Hehe.
I see. I hope it comes out nicely. Do your best, coach.
Okay, I'll do my best▼
Did you successfully teach your friend how to make pudding？
Manaka
Hmm...
Eh？ It failed？
I know that she hasn't been very good at cooking since a long time ago, but...
I think it has gone beyond my imagination...
W-What happened？
I wonder why things turned out like this. If only I could find out the reason...！
(This girl must really be the exact opposite of ▲高嶺＊＊▲)
Did you find the cause of failure for the pudding last time？
Manaka
No, I still have no clue. I've tried eating so many puddings that I think I can't possibly eat them anymore.
You've eaten so many of them...？ Well, how was the result of her latest attempt then？
Right on the passing line. I think she's going to give it to the guy today.
I see. So you've done a great job.
Hehe. Thanks. Hey, will you celebrate this with me？
Ah, okay. Where shall we go for the celebration？
I want to eat cake▼
Eh！Hmm, I thought you'd be fed up with sweets by now.
That was pudding. Cake is a completely different thing, isn't it？
Is that so...？
That is so. Hehe, let's go！
(Girls are amazing...)
Manaka
My neighbor's dog just gave birth to puppies.
Oh, how many of them？
Five, I guess. I'm going to visit them soon.
It must be fun.
Yeah. I can picture them rolling around. They must be so cute that I could eat them！ Just imagining though.
Thinking of them that I couldn't sleep.
I didn't have enough sleep but I'm not feeling tired at all！ It's just so amazing.
(You'll get very sleepy later tonight for sure.)
Manaka
I can't wait to see the puppies...
You still haven't seen those puppies yet？
Not yet. I've got a lot to do that I don't have time to visit them.
I see. By the way, On the day that we talked about this, were you okay after that？
Eh？ What do you mean？
You said that you didn't have enough sleep but you weren't tired. How was it after all？
...Well. I was so sleepy after I got home. I tried my best to stay awake until dinnertime, but...
I fell asleep while I was having dinner, just like a kid.
And Papa even recorded that on a video. I tried to delete it but he hid his camcorder somewhere.
Papa and Mama said that I was cute, but it's really embarrassing.
I have to look for it when I get home.
(I'm more interested in this video than the puppies...)
By the way, have you seen the puppies yet？
Manaka
Not yet. But I got a chance to talk to my neighbor yesterday...
"They're very healthy and naughty. It must be hard for Manaka-chan," she said.
She showed me their photos too！ They're just really cute！ And then...
▲高嶺＊＊▲, that night, you couldn't sleep, right？
...How did you know！？
I just knew it...
...I was so excited about them. I couln't help it.
(I wonder what will happen to her when she meets the puppies.)
How about the puppies？
Manaka
Well, I played with them all day long. And by the time I realized it, it was already dawn.
Eh？！
I guess I played with them too much that I ended up falling asleep.
The mother dog even came and slept next to me.
My neighbor saw it and didn't want to wake me, so she asked my Mama to let me spend the night there.
During that time, she even took a picture of me.
I want to see！
No. I was sleeping like a little kid. That was so embarrassing.
But it was really fun. My neighbor said that I should visit them again. I think I soon will.
(▲高嶺＊＊▲ is very excited about them. I guess she'll visit them again very soon...)
Manaka
I was wondering if you know any Russian cuisine.
Russian cuisine...？ Such as pierogi？ Why do you ask？
Lately, I've been into foreign foods. Now it's Russian cuisine.
Hmm. Have you tried cooking some dishes？
Yeah. I tried the boiled dumpling called pelmeni. It's stuffed with minced meat, onions, and potatoes.
Dumpling with potatoes filling？ Sounds like a croquette.
Hehe. But this one is boiled and you can eat it with sour cream sauce on top.
Sounds yummy...
It was delicious. Papa even asked for another serving of it.
I want to eat it, too...
Hehe, someday, okay？ Now I have to think what I'll make next.
Manaka
Have you heard of Janssons frestelse？
Huh？ What's that？
Hehe. It's the name of a dish.
Ah, you're still obsessed with foreign foods, huh？
That's right. This time it's Swedish food.
Hmm？ What kind of dish is it？
To make it easy for you to understand, it's quite like gratin.
It has sauteed potatoes, onions, and anchovies mixed with fresh cream and milk. Then it's baked in an oven.
...Sounds yummy.
Hehe. It was very delicious▼
I wonder what other country's food I should make next.
(I want to try someー！)
Are you still obsessed with foreign cuisine？
Manaka
Yeah. Last time, I challenged myself with a French dish.
It's called pomme souffle. It's usually served with the main dish, so it's more like a side dish, but I find it interesting.
Oh, what kind of dish is it？
It's made from potatoes and it's fried until it puffs out. I had fun making it, but it was quite difficult...
The way I sliced and stirred the ingredients and the oil's temperature. Missing any of these and it could fail.
It's made from potatoes？
Yeah. It was impossible to make it perfectly but I was quite satisfied with the result.
It's about time to look for a new recipe.
(Hmm... She's very into it...)
Hey, how's your cooking going？
Manaka
Um, it's going nicely. Last time, I tried making gnocchi. It was made with wheat flour and potatoes...
Hey, I've been concerned about it for a while. Why did you only cook potato dishes？
...You noticed？
Yeah, ever since you mentioned that souffle dish.
Actually, my aunt sent a big package of potatoes to my house. We've been giving them out but there are still a lot left.
So you tried cooking something out of them？
Yeah, I'm glad I could try making various dishes although I ended up eating them by myself.
You ate them by yourself？
Papa and Mama said they could only eat them every once in a while. So, I ate the gnocchi I made yesterday all by myself.
It was delicious. Too bad my parents couldn't eat it.
(No matter how delicious potatoes are, eating them for a whole month is a little...)
Manaka
Earlier, I went to Papa's hospital and ran into an old lady who was Papa's patient. We had a long chat.
Huh？ With your dad's patient？
Yeah, and while we were talking, more people joined us... In the end, there were as many as 7 people.
All of them were your dad's patients, eh？
I think they were.
That's why they all knew me... They mentioned some embarrassing stuff I did when I was a child.
Later, they even brought up the topic about my future husband.
They said if Mama still didn't have anyone on her mind, they'd help her find a match for me. They were so enthusiastic.
(I can picture how the scene would look like...)
Manaka
Lately, I told you about the old lady who really likes to chat, right？
Yeah, I remembered. Don't tell me you got caught up with her again.
Geez, I wouldn't get caught up that easily. I was able to leave her much earlier than last time.
Haha, okay. But why do you look so troubled now？
Um... About that...
She asked me to become her grandson's bride...
What！？
Of course, I took it as a joke and refused, but she was pressing me on meeting him at least once.
Hah, now I'm in trouble...
(The one in trouble right now is me！)
Earlier？ Ah！
Manaka
Earlier？ Oh, you mean...
...I ended up promising that lady that I would go visit her home.
Whaaaat！？
I'll go with Mama to visit that lady and her grandson.
...But then, about you being his bride...
That's not a problem... I guess.
You guess！？
Yeah, Mama will go with me, so you can rest assured.
(Whaaaat~！？)
▲高嶺＊＊▲... Speaking of which, how did it go with that lady's grandson？
Manaka
Ah！ Oh, I'm sorry. I really haven't told you, right？
Now I understand why the old lady insisted that I should meet her grandson.
Eh？
He really liked me... When I was about to leave, he didn't want to let go of my hand.
Your hand...
Hehe, he's a baby boy, so that couldn't be helped.
Huh？ A baby？
Yeah, her grandson was very cute. That's why she insisted that I should meet him.
So, that's about it. I'm sorry I made you worried.
(...But that lady might be serious about the bride thing, huh？)
Manaka
There are so many different types of magazines, right？
Yeah. If you go to a large bookstore, you can see a lot of magazines sorted by categories.
Right. Even fashion magazines have different targeted ages... It's troublesome when you can't tell them apart.
Ah, they're grouped for ages 10+, 20+, and 30+. Something like that, right？
Right. And I've notice a new vocab "Around 4" lately.
...What does that mean？
It means people around the age of 40. Hehe, it's such a strange word.
But I feel like I should start learning some of these new vocabs.
If I learn something new, I'll teach you. Let's study together.
(Do I have to study something like this too？)
Manaka
Quiz time.
Hmm？ Ah, about the fashion terms？ Okay then.
"Around 3."
If "Around 4" means people around the age of 40 then "Around 3" must be people around the age of 30, right？
Correct！ Then the next one, "B-Type."
B-Type？ Doesn't it mean blood type B？
Boo！ Then how about "conserver"？
...A console game server？
Hehe, nice guess, but wrong！
For the correct answers, "B-Type" means hip hop culture, and "conserver" is conservative fashion.
That's all. Too bad some of your answers were wrong. Hehe.
(▲高嶺＊＊▲ really studied hard.)
Did you learn any new vocabs？
Manaka
Yeah. But I only read a few magazines, so I didn't learn much.
Hmm？ So earlier, did you just buy some random magazines and read them？
Yeah, because I didn't really know which one I should read.
Wasn't that difficult？ Fashion magazines aren't that cheap.
That's not a problem, since I found out that our library also carries fashion magazines for studying purpose.
Huh？ There are magazines at the library too？
I was also surprised when I found out. They even have comics, too.
Next time, I might secretly borrow some comics...
(▲高嶺＊＊▲'s parents forbid her from reading comics, too？)
Well, do you still keep reading the fashion magazines？
Manaka
Yeah, I've read a lot of them, so I've learned many things about fashion.
But I haven't really put it into practice. There are clothes that I want, but my pocket money is limited.
I've been thinking about getting a part-time job, but that's a bit too much.
I see.
Lately, I'm enjoying reading columns about cosmetics as well.
I've never had interest in such things before...
Since I've met you, it's like my world has broadened. Thank you.
(That's something I should say to her, too...)
Manaka
Have you ever gotten caught up when you did some cleaning？
Ah, did you find some old photo albums？
Hehe. How did you know？ Were you watching me？
Bull's eyes, huh...？
I got lots of stuff, so I was thinking about sorting them out. Then I found my childhood albums and I stopped cleaning.
Okay okay, I understand.
When I realized it, it was already dark. I didn't get much done, so I'd have to do the cleaning again later.
Do you think you'll get caught up with something else next time？
Come on, don't imagine weird things.
Hey, don't jinx me like that....But I feel like it'll happen.
(I think so too...)
How was it？ Did you continue on with the cleaning？
Manaka
...It's all your fault.
W-What？
I found my diary when I was in grade school.
And then my penmanship practice book, and my ballet shoes... A lot of things.
Everything was so tempting, right？
Yeah, but I packed them all up and put them in another room. So I'll be okay next time！
...I guess. Yeah.
(I wonder...)
Did you finish cleaning？
Manaka
No, not yet.
Eh？ What could possibly get you occupied this time？
I was rearranging a lot of stuff and Mama came to see how it was going. And then we were deep in talk.
I see...
But it was fun. We talked about a lot of things.
...It was like women's private talk. There were things we couldn't say if Papa was with us.
That means, there were also things that you couldn't talk about if I was with you？
Of course. Girls always have many things to talk about.
...Could it be something about me？
Well, who knows？ It's a secret▼
(Now I'm concerned...)
How's the cleaning going？
Manaka
Well, it's finally done. My room is pretty tidy now.
I see. Good job.
Thank you. Now, it looks so different.
Anything else you're planning to do？
Yeah, from now on, I'll gradually fill up the space that I just made available.
Hmm？
That's because there are many more things that will fill my memories with you.
Eh？ Will we have that many memories together...？
We'll have many！ Hehe！
▲高嶺＊＊▲ what do you usually do before you go to bed？
Manaka
Before I go to bed...？ I do some light stretches.
Stretches？ Why？
Why？ It's what I've been doing since a long time ago.
When I stretch, it makes me feel sleepy.
even if you don't do that, ▲高嶺＊＊▲ you can always fall asleep easily anyway.
...It feels different when I stretch, and when I don't. Just a little different though.
How's that？
That's... You know... Ah, the most important thing is that I can wake up feeling refreshed！
So yeah... you should try it. You'll feel better in the morning too, okay？
(So she doesn't really know the difference, huh？)
Manaka
After the last time we talked, I stopped stretching before I went to bed.
Eh？ So you stopped stretching？
Yeah. But I think there was something different.
Well, I felt quite uneasy and it took me longer until I could sleep.
I had been stretching ever since I was in grade school. I think it helps me feel at ease...
That means there is a difference, right？
...Ah, right.
Eh？
！ Well, um... Right！ This is the difference we talked about earlier, right？
(You've just realized it now...？)
Manaka
I haven't read any novel for a long time, but I read one last night.
Ah, before bedtime？
Yeah. Somehow I really fell asleep, and I slept even deeper than when I did the stretching.
An immediate effect, huh？
But, I didn't feel refreshed when I woke up in the morning.
Haha, then for ▲高嶺＊＊▲ stretching is the best option.
I wonder. Maybe I shouldn't change my routines...
It's good to follow your habits, but sometimes a little change is good, too, right？
You think so？ ...Hmm, maybe that's true.
Manaka
Last night when I was alone, I gazed at the stars.
Before your bedtime？
Yeah, they were really beautiful. I was thinking about calling you last night, but it was already late.
Really？ It would've been nice if you and I had looked at them at the same time.
I was trying to call you by telepathy, didn't you get it？
Too bad I didn't.
Hehe, then we should practice so that we could communicate by telepathy next time.
What do you mean？
Before you go to bed, you must think about me. How's that...？
With such nice weather, we'll be able to see beautiful stars. Let's watch them together tonight.
▲高嶺＊＊▲, what do you do for fun？
Manaka
For fun？ Hmm... Like baking？
Baking？
Yeah. It's really refreshing. The kneading part is really fun. "Bamm！" I can hit the bread as hard as I want.
When I do that, even Papa and Mama try their best to stay away from the kitchen. Hehe.
I haven't baked for a while. I'll have you taste some when I do, okay？
(I wonder how her bread is going to come out...)
Thanks for the bread the other day.
Manaka
No problem. Thanks to you, I felt completely refreshed.
Does that mean... you had fun kneading the bread？ Doing that "Bamm！" thing？
Hehe, I guess so. Because no one dared to enter the kitchen.
O-Oh, I see...
I once asked Mama why she didn't join me in the kitchen.
And what did she say？
She was scared. Because I hit the bread so hard, like "Bamm！" but my face was expressionless.
But isn't that how I look when I'm getting serious with something？ What do you think？
(Um... What should I say？)
Manaka
Oh, yeah. Hey, I'm thinking of baking again. Do you have any requests？
Huh？
Hmm？
No... Just wondered if you needed some refreshing time again.
Hehe, wrong. Mama bought some natural yeast so we planned to bake some bread together.
Natural yeast？
Yeah. Yeast is necessary for baking, but I like using natural yeast the most.
Hmm... There really are a lot of varieties, huh？
Yeah, so many that I feel troubled. But once I'm obsessed, I totally can't stop.
Maybe making something delicious is my current obsession, I guess.
(You're easily obsessed with things like this, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.)
How did it go when you were baking with your mom？
Manaka
Well... Now I understand what Mama said about my expressionless face.
Eh？
Hehe. You see...
Mama's face was also expressionless when she did that "Bamm！" thing！
When I saw that, I was like "Ah, that's it." I also thought that she looked scary.
Scary？
Yes. That's why I'll never make any more bread for you in my whole life.
R-Really？
I'm kidding▼ Hehe！
Manaka
What time can you stay up until at night？
I'm not sure... Why？
Well, I'm thinking about challenging myself for my time limit.
What for？
...Well, just in case.
Just in case that we had to stay up all night, it wouldn't be good if I fell asleep first, right？
Ah, I see. But it's not good to overdo it.
And I know ▲高嶺＊＊▲, is not good at staying up late.
...That's why I need some practice.
Do you have any trick that you can teach me？ If so, I think I can do it. Do you？
(Trick？ Is there any trick for something like this？)
Manaka
Hey, I still wasn't able to stay up late at night...
You've tried this for like a whole week now. It's probably impossible.
Hah...
...Ah！ Hey, how about I exercise at night？ I'll feel refreshed and I can stay up, right？
I think it'll be the opposite. You'll feel tired and fall asleep.
...Really？
Yes. For something like this, you have to get used to it little by little.
I see... Okay, I'll do my best.
(▲高嶺＊＊▲ is really putting her effort into this, huh？)
Hey, did you succeed in extending your bedtime？
Manaka
A little bit！ One hour for now！
Oh, that's great.
Hehe. But I still feel sleepy at my usual time.
Eh？ Really？
Yeah. I have to endure it more from now on.
I even dozed off and hit my head on my desk. That was quite shocking...
But I could set a new record. Hehe！
(If you dozed off, that means you fell asleep. So it wasn't a record...)
▲高嶺＊＊▲, after that, did you try to stay up late again？
Manaka
Um... I think I should stop. I don't think it's good for me.
Did something happen？
...I told you once that I dozed off and hit my head on my desk, right？
Yeah, you did.
And this time it was so loud that Papa and Mama panicked and ran to my room.
After that, I got scolded. They told me there wasn't anything good about staying up late, and that I had to stop.
It was exactly the same as what you told me.
Yeah, and a lack of sleep isn't good for your skin. Your beautiful skin might become rough...
...Haha. Yeah, that's why I try to get enough sleep now.
I'll try my best not to keep playing throughout the night. You must cheer for me.
Of course！
Manaka
Hey, what I'm going to tell you must be kept a secret, okay？
O-Okay. What is it？
You see, well... I... have begun reading comics.
Huh？ But comics weren't allowed at ▲高嶺＊＊▲'s house, right？
It has not been clearly said but I think they're not allowed, so I secretly read them in the library.
I see... By the way, what do you read？
A comic about a female tennis player. It seems to be quite old but it's very interesting.
One time, I couldn't stop reading... I forgot about dinner.
A glutton like you did, ▲高嶺＊＊▲！？ That's really amazing！
Isn't it？ Yeah, I really wanted to read the next volume.
(For a glutton... that's amazing... Comic Power！)
Have you continued reading the comic？
Manaka
Oh, that？ Someone borrowed the comic and I haven't been able to read more.
Is that so？ By the way, what's the story about？
About a super strict coach and the intensive training he gives to this girl.
Coach, I can't do it！
...If you keep crying like this, we don't need you in our tennis club anymore. Go home！
No... For me, tennis is everything I have...
Say, it's interesting, isn't it？
(▲高嶺＊＊▲ even does a monologue？ Don't underestimate the power of comic books, huh？)
Has the comic been returned？
Manaka
Yes. It has been returned...
And？
I don't want to continue reading it.
W-Why？ You were really enjoying that comic.
At the pace I'm reading, there's only a bit more to go...
In the story, the coach and heroine separated.
After I finish reading this comic, I'm never reading another one...
Had I known that the story was going to be this sad, I wouldn't have started reading.
Hah...
(She was so into it. I kinda want to read it, too.)
How was the comic？ Did you finish reading it？
Manaka
Yeah. I couldn't resist.
How was the ending？
Happy ending. The coach returns from abroad and comes back to the heroine.
I was deeply moved and I wept quietly in the library. Hehe.
The author who could think up such story is great. I don't think I'd be able to do that.
Do you want to read another comic？
If there are other good ones. Do you know any？
Hmm, it had better be something that won't make you cry.
Then next time... Ah, but don't tell anyone about this. Also, don't tell anyone that I cried, okay？
(So this is like I'm holding one of your weaknesses？)
